properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 17 at 1:34PM PST until January 18 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected with total snow accumulation of 10 to
20 inches.

* WHERE...Olympic mountains including Hurricane Ridge.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 4 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible. Gusty
winds could bring down tree branches.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow level will rise from below 1000
feet this evening to around 3000 feet Saturday.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 PM PST SATURDAY ABOVE 2000 FEET
